Cambium Learning Group, Inc.

17855 Dallas Parkway, Suite 400 
Dallas TX 75287 United States
Phone: +1 214-___-____
Fax: +1 214-___-____
http://www.cambiumlearning.com





16
Managers




100
IT employees




$22.2MEST.
IT Budget




Cambium Learning Group, Inc. develops and delivers intervention curricula, educational technologies, and other research-based education solutions for students. Its Voyager segment offers reading, math, and professional development programs focused on at-risk and special education students. The Cambium Learning brands include… MoreCambium Learning Group, Inc. develops and delivers intervention curricula, educational technologies, and other research-based education solutions for students. Its Voyager segment offers reading, math, and professional development programs focused on at-risk and special education students. The Cambium Learning brands include Sopris West Educational Services, Intellitools, Inc, Kurzweil Educational Systems, and Metropolitan Teaching and Learning.
Internal information technology operations at Cambium Learning Group largely exist to directly support its subsidiaries' educational technology products and websites. All subsidiaries, of which Voyager is the largest, handle their own product-related technology operations; employees of the parent company perform… MoreInternal information technology operations at Cambium Learning Group largely exist to directly support its subsidiaries' educational technology products and websites. All subsidiaries, of which Voyager is the largest, handle their own product-related technology operations; employees of the parent company perform all other IT operations.

Cambium Learning Group has consolidated its enterprise systems into a cohesive and flexible platform using the JD Edwards EnterpriseOne ERP system integrated with Salesforce.com. Other production- and website-supportive business systems and platforms are developed and maintained by the same groups that handle the subsidiaries' client-facing development operations.

  Cambium Learning Group, Inc. not is planning to increase security spending.  The company has recently completed deploying a federated identity security solution, threat and intrusion detection technologies, and next-generation firewall solutions. It uses F5 BigIP as its storage security solution, and has no fraud detection solution. Cambium Learning Group's security safeguards include regular policy reviews, inventory of personal employee and customer data, documented incident response process, and malware and virus protection software on all devices; it also has a documented incident response process, a regular compliance review process, and a continuous compliance model in place.  The company uses a home-grown solution to monitor threats across its networks, security devices and data. 

The company is currently evaluating cloud solutions for a possible implementation.  It currently runs business applications, email, accounting, financials, storage, and backup in a cloud environment, and senior sources report maintaining 100% site uptime are the company's biggest cloud related security concerns.     To help store the large amount of information generated through these business systems, Cambium Learning Group has moved several databases to the cloud. These databases are based out of seven servers, some of which are virtualized. The company also maintains an additional seven development and backup servers. 

Infrastructure operations, including telecommunications operations, network services, data services, technical support, and desktop support, are handled by a small team of IT professionals.

Cambium Learning Group, Inc. has noted that it anticipates IT security spending to increase on perimeter and storage security, and infrastructure expenditures to increase for data storage, network performance and management, remote access control, data center infrastructure, network security, capacity planning, disaster recovery, and virtualization. 

The company has deployed IP KVM technology, switched APC power, and SSL VPN appliances at its data center. It has also implemented cloud-based platform and infrastructure services to reduce its use of human capital while increasing productivity. Cambium Learning Group has also deployed business line, productivity, analytics, and business-to-consumer mobile applications. 

The company's file sharing and code deployments across its wide area network (WAN) and its time and expense system cause the most strain on its network environment. 

The IT budget is typically finalized in Q4.





