 What people are saying about Cambium Learning:


                	As a school system with a long track record with Kurzweil 3000, we've seen students' reading skills increase by as much as 2 or 3 grade levels within a single semester. Tom Turner, School Administrator, Chouteau Public Schools, Chouteau, OK


                	One Gizmo in the hand of a math or science teacher can provide almost limitless opportunities for conceptual and extended learning. Leslie Accardo, Model Schools Coordinator, Lower Hudson Regional Information Center, NY


                	The support we receive from our Voyager Sopris partners has consistently been reliable, professional, and personal.  I appreciate their eagerness�to assist our district with problem solving and building internal capacity. Deanna Parish, Coordinator of Curriculum & Instruction, Department of Exceptional Children Services,Charleston County School District, SC




                	My class of kindergarten students LOVE going on Raz-Kids. Often, they go there for their free time play. They are highly motivated to read and I find it a wonderful way to get leveled books into the hands of my early readers. Bless you all, for what you are providing for education! Birdy Hartman, Teacher, San Diego, CA


                	Our teachers are completely behind Reflex because they are seeing an amazing change in our students' math skills. Mary Armstrong, Math Instructional Facilitator, Bryant School District 25, AR















Cambium Learning Group - Wikipedia





















 






Cambium Learning Group

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search






This article needs additional citations for verification. Please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources. Unsourced material may be challenged and removed. (May 2010) (Learn how and when to remove this template message)



Cambium Learning Group


Type

Public


Traded as
NASDAQ: ABCD


Divisions
Voyager Sopris
Kurzweil
ExploreLearning
Learning A-Z


Website
www.cambiumlearningtechnologies.com


Cambium Learning Group is an American company which creates computer software and hardware products serving students ranging from pre-kindergarten to adult; and enabling educators who help them learn.
In December, 2009, Cambium acquired Voyager Learning Company.
The company's business units are Voyager, Sopris and Cambium Learning Technologies, which itself has four divisions:

Learning A-Z – Research-based online curriculum resources for differentiated instruction in reading, writing, and science (grades K-6)
Kurzweil Educational Systems – Reading, study skill, and writing support software for learners and text-to-speech software for the blind/visually-impaired (grade 3-adult)
ExploreLearning – Interactive online math and science simulations (grades 3-12).
Voyager Sopris – Innovative, evidence-based instructional solutions and services.

External links[edit]

Cambium Learning Technologies website
Cambium Learning Group - About page
Voyager Sopris Learning website
Kurzweil 3000 and 1000, grade 3 through adult literacy assistives
IntelliTools: Classroom Suite, IntelliKeys, MathPad, switches, Prek through 5 accessibility and accessible educational software





